{
  "body": "I am grateful for the latest switch to atom highlighter, however, with current CSS the code is significantly harder to read.\r\n\r\nFor example, comments are ``#888`` on ``#CFCFCF``, this is not very readable. ``#489047`` is not very nice as well.\r\n\r\nSo I suggest to change both the background color for snippets and code colors to add more contrast. You can use one of the contrast checkers ([1](http://contrastchecker.com/), [2](http://leaverou.github.io/contrast-ratio/), [3](http://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/), [4](https://snook.ca/technical/colour_contrast/colour.html#fg=33FF33,bg=333333), â€¦)  to verify the results.",
